Since we use JIRA with over 500 Users and bought a Confluence-License for 10 $ to evaluate the software, we're not able to add or edit content in Confluence because we imported those 500 Users.

We'd really like to deactivate all users but 2-3 at once. But that's not working currently without openig each user and deactive them.

(We're currently running 5.1.5, but this problem will occur in the other versions as well.)

While researching CONF-26542, we discovered that emails generated by confluence don't contain i18n resolved WebItemModuleDescriptor keys. See the example below:

{code}
Content-Type: image/png; name=mention.mail.templates.action.view.page
Content-Transfer-Encoding: base64
Content-ID: <mention.mail.templates.action.view.page>
Content-Disposition: attachment; 
	filename=mention.mail.templates.action.view.page
{code}

Although CONF-26542 is currently causing issues for Amazon SES, we suspect that this issue would need to be resolved before that one can be addressed. This issue may also affect other mail clients that attempt to do security protection against files with multiple dots (to prevent attacks like vacation-images.zip.exe)

